CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 28, 1974, pg. 1 reads: "Closing The Doors - Emma Lucas, a counsellor [sic] with the local Planned Parenthood Center, is posting the familiar "Closed Door" sign at the Hill House office of the family planning agency. A similar action took place at the Wilkinsburg branch.  Both were facilities that served largely poor and Black clientelle [sic] - Harris photo"
TitMainTitle: Emma Lucas hanging "closed" sign on room 158, with drawing of mother and child mounted on wall, at Planned Parenthood Center, Hill House office
